OL,3,CMinister: 'Funding for Jersey's health
OL,4,Cservice may have to change'
OL,6,FDeputy Binet adds: "Health is spending
OL,7,Fmore money than we thought and we are
OL,8,Fprobably going to require #24 million
OL,9,Fmore this year than budgeted, and the
OL,10,Fsame next year.
OL,12,F"We are never going to save money to
OL,13,Fthe extent we can come back from that.
OL,15,F"Some of that budget does include work
OL,16,Fon bringing wait times down. The short
OL,17,Fterm is to make sure we have the
OL,18,Ffunding we need for 2025."
