OL,3,CMinister: 'Funding for Jersey's health
OL,4,Cservice may have to change'
OL,6,FOne criticism of the Beveridge Model
OL,7,Fis its potential risk of people
OL,8,Foverusing services.
OL,10,FWithout restrictions, free access
OL,11,Fpotentially allows patients to demand
OL,12,Fhealthcare that is unnecessary or
OL,13,Fwasteful. The result would be rising
OL,14,Fcosts and higher taxes.
OL,16,FThe NHS is used by the United Kingdom,
OL,17,FSpain, New Zealand, Cuba, Hong Kong
OL,18,Fand the Veterans Health Administration
OL,19,Fin the United States of America.
