OL,6,FThe Bismarck Model (Public Health
OL,7,FInsurance)
OL,9,FEmployers and workers are responsible
OL,10,Ffor paying for their health insurance
OL,11,Fsystem through payroll deductions that
OL,12,Fcreate 'sickness funds'.
OL,14,FThey cover every employed person,
OL,15,Fregardless of pre-existing conditions,
OL,16,Fand are not profit-based.
OL,18,FProviders and hospitals are generally
OL,19,Fprivate, although insurers are public.
