OL,4,Cservice may have to change'
OL,6,FThe primary criticism of the National
OL,7,FHealth Insurance Model is the
OL,8,Fpotential for long waiting lists and
OL,9,Fdelays in treatment, which are
OL,10,Fconsidered a serious health policy
OL,11,Fissue.
OL,13,FThis system is used in Canada and
OL,14,FTaiwan and is similar to Medicare in
OL,15,FAmerica.
OL,17,FThe Out-of-Pocket Model
OL,19,FPatients must pay for the procedures
OL,20,Fand services they need and rely on
OL,21,Fsavings or private health insurance.
